wikipedia_page.main: John William Buckley (24 November 1903 – 13 April 1985) was an English footballer who made 349 appearances in the Football League playing for Doncaster Rovers and Lincoln City. He then moved into non-league football with Grantham, with whom he came runner-up in the Midland League in 1936–37. He played as a right back.
